item.description: I can already see the prescriptive comments; yeah, so I know... I‚Äôm a smoker. From what I‚Äôve been led to believe, there‚Äôs actually an entire fetish subcategory structured around sultry women smoking sultrily. I‚Äôve never gotten it myself, but to each their own ‚Äî Rule 34 is a good rule in every case, provided it involves consenting adults and doesn‚Äôt hurt anyone. In any case, I‚Äôm winding down my smoking years. Back in my 20s, I was a social smoker, usually when going out to bars with friends. Then, I did the usual amount to be expected from a person who smokes for several years. The last year and a half? I would be lying if I said that nicotine hasn‚Äôt just fucking gotten me through a lot of days. Public service announcements, ad campaigns, peer pressure, establishing rules on when and where you can buy tobacco, or in which places you can and can‚Äôt smoke it‚Ä¶ there‚Äôs not a lot of empirical evidence to support the claim that any of those things actually deter smoking. The one thing that really works? Charging out the ass for it. Ask anybody who lives in the city of Philadelphia, New York, or for god sakes, London? They‚Äôll tell you the reason they quit was the price hike. (¬£18 for a pack of American Spirits? If you‚Äôre a pack a day person, that‚Äôs... about $9,000/year for you Yankee followers out there. Couple of years, that‚Äôs a brand-new, souped-up Camry.) I will soon be living in a place with such prohibitive pricing, so like many before me, I‚Äôll be saying farewell to the monkey. It‚Äôs probs for the best anyway: I‚Äôm pushing 38, and ain‚Äôt as young as I used to be. Shit catches up with you. I can promise you one thing, though: when I formally join the ranks of the ex-smokers of the world, I will never be one of those people who walks up to a complete stranger and says, ‚ÄúYoU kNoW tHaT‚Äôs bAd FoR yOu, RiGht???‚Äù Isn‚Äôt it funny, that the only people who do that are people who literally spent decades feeding the beast? item.title: heatherwiththebeck on Instagram [VIDEO]
item.description: Was just composing a mini-essay about fear (for the Patreon ‚Äî link in bio). We literally, all of us, have a big fear. Don‚Äôt be macho. You know you do, too. Snakes are cool. I like them, actually. In Spain, there are about a dozen that are dangerous. About a year ago, when it was dry and the critters came near the house, I felled a legit asp. Fucking felt like a badass. I used to be afraid of wasps. Not bees, or even extremely white people (though these days...) but the godless killing machines that don‚Äôt pollinate or make honey. But living in Spain? If you can‚Äôt take the heat, get out of the kitchen! Those fuckers are everywhere. As was the case when I forced myself to love coconuts back in 2010 (it always bugged me that there was only ONE food I ever hated), I forced myself to tolerate wasps. Like one of those old ladies from ‚ÄúMad Max: Fury Road.‚Äù But with wasps, and not cartoonish hypermasculinity. Which brings me to my last remaining fear that I have. At least for the time being. As a certain lady (who I posted about on Patreon yesterday) has pointed out... vertigo. Yeah! So what?! Really high places are the devil, and I have a healthy sense of self preservation. Yup. Sticking to it. Though... she did say she would do something really special/neat for/to me if I stood on this one particular wall... There might be rum involved? Sooo... we‚Äôll see. üòè
